title: The anatomy of nature (Photo Art Philosophy Ebook).pdf
description:
The anatomy of nature - how function shapes the form and design of animate and inanimate structures throughout the universe.

bY aNDREAS fEININGER

Crown / 1956 / PDF / English / 169 pages / 40.2 MB

Collecting his best nature photographs, Life photographer Andreas Feininger has used them to illustrate the theory that function shapes form--from whole valleys and rocks to feathers, bones or molecules. At the back is an illustrated section dealing with the special techniques used in nature photography. 168 pages; 176 b&w reproductions
